{
  "text": "In a previous study we established that human FMs from normal term pregnancies constitutively express the viral sensors, TLR3 and TLR8, as well as the TLR adapter proteins MyD88 and TRIF [CITATION_1] . Therefore, in this study, FMs were treated with the TLR3 agonist, Poly(I:C), and the TLR8 agonist, viral ssRNA [CITATION_2] . After treatment with Poly(I:C), FMs secreted significantly higher levels of TNF-a (2.1-fold), MIP-1a (8-fold), MIP-1b (4.8-fold), and RANTES (16.4-fold) compared with the NT control. In parallel, FM secretion of IL-2, and VEGF was significantly dampened by 4-fold and 4.1-fold, respectively, after exposure to Poly(I:C) (Fig. 1) . FM secretion of IL-1b, IL-6, G-CSF, MCP-1, GRO-a, IL-8, GM-CSF and IFNg were not significantly changed after Poly(I:C) treatment (Fig. 1) . After treatment with viral ssRNA, FMs secreted significantly higher levels of IL-1b (13.8-fold), IL-2 (1.3-fold), IL-6 (4.1-fold), TNF-a (4.2-fold), MCP-1 (1.9-fold), G-CSF (3.8-fold), MIP-1a (4.8-fold), , RANTES (4.3-fold) and GRO-a (6.6-fold) (Fig. 1) . FM secretion of IL-8, GM-CSF, IFNg and VEGF were not significantly changed after ssRNA treatment (Fig. 1) . Levels of IL-4, IL-10, IL-12 and IL-17 were below the assay's detection limit.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "43611588",
    "[CITATION_2]": "42000671"
